I wanted to "fail fast" by removing unavailable characters instead of trying to approximate them. Does that sound reasonable or would you still prefer removing diacritical marks of characters not in ISO 8859-1?', 'Thanks for your contribution @tobifasc , this is now merged and will be shipped for the next 7.0.x maintenance release.

The PR is marked as "closed" because I had to amend and rebase your commit. In the future, you can avoid that by always submitting a PR from a branch on your fork (i.e. not `main`).']

